details.description: Borboleta Café is a vibrant, community-focused coffee shop located in the heart of Rock Hill, SC. Our mission is to create a welcoming, safe space where coffee lovers can connect, grow, and be inspired. We proudly serve high-quality, locally roasted coffee from Pure Intentions and offer a menu full of carefully crafted espresso drinks, teas, fresh pastries, and more. Whether you're looking to fuel your day with a delicious cup of coffee, attend one of our financial literacy workshops, or simply enjoy a cozy corner to relax- Borboleta Café is here to nourish your body and mind.

reviews_data.review_text:
Forget the other coffee places in Rock Hill... dont even think about trying to find a better place in Charlotte. This is the spot!

Coffee is amazing! The temperature is fantastic, and the flavor is amazing.

This is the ambrosia of the gods!

Oh, and flavor wise, the coffee isn't sour and tastes like actual coffee, not burnt like Dunkin or Starbucks! It's local and independently owned.

Oh, and atmosphere! Calm music, great little tables, and chairs i could spend hours here just working.

Don't even worry about parking. You have a whole parking lot to choose from.

Now there are cons... I want more couches to lounge in while I read... I know picky picky me, but hey, I can always ask.

Love this place! (^_^)/"
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you so much for your incredible review! We’re beyond grateful for your support and love hearing that our coffee and atmosphere hit the mark for you.

Forget the other coffee places in Rock Hill... dont even think about trying to find a better place in Charlotte. This is the spot!

Coffee is amazing! The temperature is fantastic, and the flavor is amazing.

This is the ambrosia of the gods!

Oh, and flavor wise, the coffee isn't sour and tastes like actual coffee, not burnt like Dunkin or Starbucks! It's local and independently owned.

Oh, and atmosphere! Calm music, great little tables, and chairs i could spend hours here just working.

Don't even worry about parking. You have a whole parking lot to choose from.

Now there are cons... I want more couches to lounge in while I read... I know picky picky me, but hey, I can always ask.

Love this place! (^_^)/"
